  "summary": "Multiple vulnerabilities in Rsync",
  "details": "Rsync versions 3.3.0 and earlier are affected by six vulnerabilities including heap buffer overflow, information disclosure, arbitrary file disclosure, path traversal, safe-links bypass, and a symbolic-link race condition. Depending on deployment, these flaws can lead to remote code execution, arbitrary file read/write, and privilege escalation.",
